# CODEOWNERS - auto-assigns human reviewers to PRs (Tenacious Standard §1, §2).
# Fixes the "no human review" gap: a human is pulled onto sensitive changes.
#
# ============================================================================
# THIS IS A PLACEHOLDER. Each project is owned by a DIFFERENT team, so the
# reviewers below MUST be set per project. Two ways to do that:
#
#   1. Manually: replace the owners below with this project's real GitHub
#      team(s) (e.g. @get10acious/team-alpha) or individual @usernames.
#
#   2. Automatically: The Tacit's bootstrapper fills this in when the project
#      is onboarded, using the team / Tech Lead / Project Owner recorded for
#      that specific project - so each team's project routes reviews to that
#      team. (The template can't know the team; the central system does.)
#
# Until set, replace every @ORG/<team> with a real team or @username.
# ============================================================================

# Default owner for everything (this project's team).
*                   @ORG/PROJECT_TEAM

# Sensitive surfaces (Standard §1 risk areas) - require closer review.
**/auth/**          @ORG/PROJECT_TECH_LEADS
**/security/**      @ORG/PROJECT_TECH_LEADS
**/migrations/**    @ORG/PROJECT_TECH_LEADS
**/alembic/**       @ORG/PROJECT_TECH_LEADS
/.github/**         @ORG/PROJECT_TECH_LEADS

# Highest-risk areas - Tech Lead + Project Owner (rename to your folders).
**/billing/**       @ORG/PROJECT_TECH_LEADS @ORG/PROJECT_OWNERS
**/payments/**      @ORG/PROJECT_TECH_LEADS @ORG/PROJECT_OWNERS
